{"key":"processedPost-6161465","value":{"id":6161465,"first":5455843,"last":6161465,"when":1160667987,"utime":"10/12/06 06:46 PM","content":"You shouldn't dry mushrooms in anything but open air or a dehydrator.  Just lay them out on paper towels or cardboard in the open, with a fan blowing on them.  They'll be dry in 24 to 36 hours, then put on desiccant to get the last of the moisture out.  Any mushroom that has been picked a week ago and is still wet is a case of food poisoning waiting to happen.  <br />RR","title":"Re: Rotten Shrooms??","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}